HEADWORD: Pyrus
<hw>Py"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pyrus</ets>, or better <ets>pirus</ets>, pear tree.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of rosaceous trees and shrubs having
pomes for fruit. It includes the apple, crab apple, pear, chokeberry,
sorb, and mountain ash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyruvic</ent>⟦br⟧
